  "texts": [
    "It is challenging for NER researchers to develop a corpus in low-resources languages.",
    "NER research application domainNER application covers both general and specific domains.",
    "NER, in a general domain, is responsible for recognizing entities such as a person (PER), location (LOC), and organization (ORG) recognition.",
    "As seen in Table 5, there are 137 of 190 titles in a general domain.",
    "NER in specific domains include medical and health, biomedical and chemical, network and security, biology, chemistry, geoscience, business and economics, history and culture, sport science, military, and agricultural."
  ]
